      <h5 class="header">THE JOURNAL TEMPLATE</h5>
      <p><a name="_GoBack"></a> This simple journal template will help give you some structure in how best you can document your journey. Journaling is a powerful tool and I really recommend that on top of using the table I gave you earlier, that you also journal on the completion of each step using this template: 
      <ul>
         <li>Step Number</li>
         <li>amount intention was for</li>
         <li>Amount that showed up</li>
         <li>How you felt as it showed upv
         <li>How you celebrated &ndash; how did it feel?</li>
         <li>Who you shared the news of the success with and why</li>
         <li>How much you are setting an intention for now</li>
         <li>How you feel going into the next step</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Notice that this does not mention the date &ndash; I don&rsquo;t want you to get caught up in how long each step takes! The less you give energy to the idea of time, the less of a hold it has on you!</p>
